                  "paragraphOrdinal": 5,
                  "paragraphTitle": null,
                  "paragraphSubtitles": [],
                  "paragraphContents": [
                    "Conditional sentences usually have two clauses: the if-clause and the main clause. To make a second conditional sentence, we use:",
                    "If + simple past and would + base form"
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "paragraphOrdinal": 6,
                  "paragraphTitle": null,
                  "paragraphSubtitles": [],
                  "paragraphContents": [
                    "We can use other modal verbs (for example, can, could, might, should) instead of would in the main clause."
                  ]
